content: I've also been attending comedy shows at different venues around the city, and last weekend I saw a great show at the Improv with a headlining act who's one of my favorite comedians. I've been trying to write jokes every day, even if it's just for 10-15 minutes, to keep my creative juices flowing. Do you have any tips on how to structure a comedy set, like how to transition between jokes and how to end strong?
